// lifecycle_entry_unload.ember — regression for the @entry return-sign bug
// surfaced by demo/game. @entry returning <= 0 means UNLOAD (docs/LIFECYCLE.md
// §1): the host must NOT start the --tick loop. Before the fix, the CLI's
// `exit_code = int(r & 0x7fffffff)` clamp turned a negative return (e.g. -1)
// into a large positive (0x7fffffff), so `entry_says_stay = exit_code > 0`
// was TRUE and the tick thread started anyway — ticking a module that had
// asked to unload. The fix uses the SIGNED return for the lifecycle decision.
//
// This script returns -1 (unload) but declares an @on_tick that, if the bug
// regressed, would run and print "stopped after N ticks". The harness asserts
// the run does NOT print "stopped after" (no tick) and DOES print the
// "module unloaded (no tick)" line.
@on_tick
fn tick() -> i64 { return 1; }

@entry
fn main() -> i64 { return -1; }
